    <title>Combined summary - Batch exchange withdrawal to lightning requires covenants</title>
    <updated>2023-10-25T01:58:59.977155+00:00</updated>
    <link href="https://lists.linuxfoundation.org/pipermail/lightning-dev/2023-October/004179.html" rel="alternate"/>
    <summary>The email discusses the challenges in designing a protocol for lightning withdrawals from exchanges. One of the main issues is that a withdrawal transaction must be signed before the commitment transaction is broadcasted. To address this, the email proposes using covenants, specifically `SIGHASH_ANYPREVOUT`, to make signatures valid for spending from the batch transaction. The sender acknowledges the need for a solution to address security concerns and hopes that others may come up with a solution. Overall, the email presents a proposal for minimizing on-chain footprint in lightning withdrawals and highlights the limitations of the current approach.</summary>
